shoot:description:To start things off for May I have a few photos from a nice walk down at the wetlands.  There were some cooperative (for photography) birds including Common Yellowthroat, Black Tern, Bald Eagle, and Black-bellied Plover, but the highlight for me was well more than a dozen Black-necked Stilts!  I'd never seen so many in one day.  I managed to get fairly low for some of the shots, and got lucky with a gap in the grasses.  I later learned that the ones with a brownish color to their backs are females, and many of these photos are of a male and female together.
shoot:favorite:2026-05-01-103032-18-R5PT1821-sm.jpg
2026-05-01-102747-05-R5PT1661-sm.jpg:description:I left the camera is 1.6x "crop" mode here but still managed to fit all four stilts in the same frame.  There was also a Long-billed Dowitcher hiding there as well, which I didn't even see while editing the photo!
